* as fs from 'node:fs/promises'\\nimport * as path from 'node:path'\\n\\nimport initSqlJs from 'sql.js'\\nimport * as vscode from 'vscode'\\n\\nlet adapter: initSqlJs.SqlJsStatic &#124; null = null\\nlet dbPath: string &#124; null = null\\n\\nexport async function initDB(context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {\\n  if (!adapter &#124;&#124; !dbPath) {\\n    adapter = await initSqlJs()\\n    dbPath = getDatabasePath(context)\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nasync function getDB() {\\n  if (!adapter &#124;&#124; !dbPath) {\\n    throw new Error('DB not initialized')\\n  }\\n  const buffer = await fs.readFile(dbPath)\\n  return new adapter.Database(buffer)\\n}\\n\\nfunction getDatabasePath(context: vscode.ExtensionContext): string {\\n  const globalStoragePath = context.globalStorageUri.fsPath\\n\\n  // Navigate up to Cursor's User/globalStorage directory\\n  // From: /path/to/Cursor/User/globalStorage/publisher.extension-name\\n  // To:   /path/to/Cursor/User/globalStorage/state.vscdb\\n  const cursorGlobalStorage = path.join(globalStoragePath, '..', 'state.vscdb')\\n\\n  return path.resolve(cursorGlobalStorage)\\n}\\n\\nexport type DBRow = {\\n  key: string\\n  value?: string\\n}\\n\\nexport async function getRowsByLike({\\n  key,\\n  value,\\n  keyOnly = false,\\n}: {\\n  key: string\\n  value?: string\\n  keyOnly?: boolean\\n}): Promise<DBRow[]> {\\n  if (!key) {\\n    throw new Error('key cannot be null')\\n  }\\n\\n  const db = await getDB()\\n  let query = `SELECT key${keyOnly ? **Document Database Schema**: Describe the tables, columns, and data types used in Cursor's internal SQLite database\n2. **Map Relationships**: Explain the relationships between different tables and how data is connected\n3. **Guide Development**: Provide a reference for developers working on the extension to understand how to query and extract data\n4. **Maintain Compatibility**: Track changes in the database structure across different Cursor versions\n\n## Background\n\nCursor stores various data in an internal SQLite database, including:\n- Chat conversations and message history\n- AI interactions and completions\n- User preferences and settings\n- Workspace-specific data\n- Usage metrics and telemetry\n\nThis extension accesses this database directly to collect and process relevant information for analysis and monitoring purposes.\n\n## Structure\n\nThis documentation should cover:\n\n- **Tables**: Detailed descriptions of each table in the database\n- **Columns**: Data types, constraints, and purposes of each column\n- **Relationships**: Foreign keys and logical relationships between tables\n- **Queries**: Common query patterns for extracting specific data\n- **Version Changes**: Notes on how the database structure evolves across Cursor versions\n\n## Contributing\n\nWhen updating this documentation:\n- Verify information against the actual database Cursor Tab Autocompletion Extraction\n\nThis document describes how to extract autocompletions from Cursor Tab embedded plugin logs.\n\n## Overview\n\nCursor Tab logs contain model output with code changes in a custom diff-like format. These logs can be accessed through the VS Code API by connecting to the appropriate output channel.\n\n### Accessing the Output Channel\n\n```typescript\nimport * as vscode from 'vscode';\n\n// Get the Cursor Tab output channel\nconst outputChannel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('cursor-tab');\n\n// Listen to output\nconst disposable = vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument((event) => {\n  if (event.document.uri.scheme === 'output') {\n    // Parse the log content\n    const content = event.document.getText();\n  }\n});\n```\n\n## Log Format\n\nThe logs contain entries prefixed with `=======>Model output` followed by diff blocks showing code additions and deletions:\n\n- Lines prefixed with `-&#124;` indicate removed code\n- Lines prefixed with `+&#124;` indicate added code\n- Each diff block begins with `@@` followed by file path and line number\n\n## Example Log Entry\n\n```\n2025-10-31 15:20:14.308 [info] =======>Model output \n@@ src/uploader.ts:33\n-&#124;export function uploadChange(change: ProcessedChange) {\n+&#124;export function uploadChange(change: ProcessedChange) {\n+&#124;  return {\n+&#124;    blame: change.blame,\n+&#124;    prompt: change.prompt,\n+&#124;    inference: change.inference,\n+&#124;    aiResponseAt: change.createdAt.toISOString(),\n+&#124;    model: change.model,\n+&#124;    toolName: 'Cursor',\n+&#124;  }\n+&#124;}\n```\n\n## Implementation Requirements\n\nTo extract autocompletions:\n\n1. Connect to the Cursor Tab output channel using the VS Code API\n2. Parse log entries marked with `=======>Model output`\n3. Extract code additions (lines prefixed with `+&#124;`) from the diff blocks\n4. Cursor Tab Autocompletion Extraction\n\nThis document describes how to extract autocompletions from Cursor Tab embedded plugin logs.\n\n## Overview\n\nCursor Tab logs contain model output with code changes in a custom diff-like format. These logs can be accessed through the VS Code API by connecting to the appropriate output channel.\n\n### Accessing the Log Manually\n\n1. Press `Cmd+Shift+P` (macOS) or `Ctrl+Shift+P` (Windows/Linux)\n2. Select \"Cursor Tab\" from the dropdown\n\n### Accessing the Output Channel Programmatically\n\n```typescript\nimport * as vscode from 'vscode';\n\n// Get the Cursor Tab output channel\nconst outputChannel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('cursor-tab');\n\n// Listen to output\nconst disposable = vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument((event) => {\n  if (event.document.uri.scheme === 'output') {\n    // Parse the log content\n    const content = event.document.getText();\n  }\n});\n```\n\n## Log Format\n\nThe logs contain entries prefixed with `=======>Model output` followed by diff blocks showing code additions and deletions:\n\n- Lines prefixed with `-&#124;` indicate removed code\n- Lines prefixed with `+&#124;` indicate added code\n- Each diff block begins with `@@` followed by file path and line number\n\n## Example Log Entry\n\n```\n2025-10-31 15:20:14.308 [info] =======>Model output \n@@ src/uploader.ts:33\n-&#124;export function uploadChange(change: ProcessedChange) {\n+&#124;export function uploadChange(change: ProcessedChange) {\n+&#124;  return {\n+&#124;    blame: change.blame,\n+&#124;    prompt: change.prompt,\n+&#124;    inference: change.inference,\n+&#124;    aiResponseAt: change.createdAt.toISOString(),\n+&#124;    model: change.model,\n+&#124;    toolName: 'Cursor',\n+&#124;  }\n+&#124;}\n```\n\n## Implementation Requirements\n\nTo extract autocompletions:\n\n1. Connect to the Cursor Tab output channel using the VS Code API\n2. Parse log entries marked with `=======>Model output`\n3. Extract code additions (lines prefixed with `+&#124;`) from the diff blocks\n4. Select \\\"Cursor Tab\\\" from the dropdown\\n\\n### Accessing the Output Channel Programmatically\\n\\n```typescript\\nimport * as vscode from 'vscode';\\n\\n// Get the Cursor Tab output channel\\nconst outputChannel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('cursor-tab');\\n\\n// Listen to output\\nconst disposable = vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument((event) => {\\n  if (event.document.uri.scheme === 'output') {\\n    // Parse the log content\\n    const content = event.document.getText();\\n  }\\n});\\n```\\n\\n## Log Format\\n\\nThe logs contain entries prefixed with `=======>Model output` followed by diff blocks showing code additions and deletions:\\n\\n- Lines prefixed with `-&#124;` indicate removed code\\n- Lines prefixed with `+&#124;` indicate added code\\n- Each diff block begins with `@@` followed by file path and line number\\n\\n## Example Log Entry\\n\\n```\\n2025-10-31 15:20:14.308 [info] =======>Model output \\n@@ src/uploader.ts:33\\n-&#124;export function uploadChange(change: ProcessedChange) {\\n+&#124;export function uploadChange(change: ProcessedChange) {\\n+&#124;  return {\\n+&#124;    blame: change.blame,\\n+&#124;    prompt: change.prompt,\\n+&#124;    inference: change.inference,\\n+&#124;    aiResponseAt: change.createdAt.toISOString(),\\n+&#124;    model: change.model,\\n+&#124;    toolName: 'Cursor',\\n+&#124;  }\\n+&#124;}\\n```\\n\\n## Implementation Requirements\\n\\nTo extract autocompletions:\\n\\n1. Connect to the Cursor Tab output channel using the VS Code API\\n2. Parse log entries marked with `=======>Model output`\\n3. Extract code additions (lines prefixed with `+&#124;`) from the diff blocks\\n4. Parse file paths and line numbers from the `@@` headers\\n\"}"},"checkpointId":"973a07cb-9ea8-4da8-add4-6b75989af619"}|
